 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Holy Paladin Phase 2 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 276 top-ranked Holy Paladin healing parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 2 (Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Holy Paladin items in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Boots of Courage Unending (86%), Crystalforge Pauldrons (72%), Aegis of the Vindicator (65%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Holy Paladin use in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Bracing Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Teardrop Living Ruby in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Holy Paladin need in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "11 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Renewal on head, Greater Inscription of Faith on shoulders, Golden Spellthread on legs and Enchant Weapon - Major Healing on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Renewal comes from Quartermaster — Hellfire Peninsula."
  }
 ]
